subSubSection.paragraph:
Type locality.
“ Sierra Leone ” (
Clytra intersecta
); „Rhobomp, Sierra Leone “ (
Gynandrophthalma seminigra
).

Male (
Fig. 8
). Labrum transverse, anterior margin widely shallowly incised, the lateral parts of anterior margin with short pale hairs, several longer hairs also on the disc of labrum. Head semiopaque. Anterior part of head covered with fine punctures, almost glabrous. Frons very broad, 3.7 times as wide as the diameter of the eye, with a round shallow impression in the middle, densely covered with relatively large punctures and short recumbent hairs. Vertex finely punctured, with dense long pale hairs. Antennomere 1 clavate, anteriorly covered with longer hairs, antennomere 4 small, triangular, antennae distinctly serrated from segment 5 .
